I think that, if it hasn't already been done, it's important that you know that you will always come across people who won't necessarily agree with your choices, who won't like your style, your expressions, or something else... but, never stop believing in yourself, stay true to who you are, with your personality and sensitivity that charmed the jury; Another thing, it's not given to everyone, to dare! It will allow you to move forward and honestly, I can only note that you fit with any repertoire, I even find your versions sometimes better than the original! You seem humble and deeply kind, you have talent and generosity, you weren't part of what I would have bet on at first and honestly, I don't remember not appreciating one of your performances, I find you astonishing... to finish, I really loved your interpretation of Gainsbourg, I loved the original too but for once I heard the lyrics clearly, we might have had the impression that you were careful not to make any expressions, you transmitted emotion to me through my television so I don't understand why three members of the jury didn't feel it! Anyway, I wish you lots of good things, keep your feet on the ground, don't change who you are, stay humble, stay you, make good use of constructive criticism and don't pay attention to the ones that aren't
